'''Rodrigo Zalazar Martínez''' (born 12 August 1999) is a Uruguayan professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|565522}}</ref><ref name="auf">{{cite web|title=8 - Rodrigo Zalazar|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/8-rodrigo-zalazar/|accessdate=27 July 2019}}</ref> He will join [[Sporting CP]] on 1 July 2026.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Zalazar joined the youth categories of [[Albacete Balompié]] in 2007, aged eight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/internacional/rodrigo-zalazar-talento-uruguayo-cultivado-en-albacete-n/|title=Rodrigo Zalazar: talento uruguayo cultivado en Albacete|trans-title=Rodrigo Zalazar: Uruguayan talent raised at Albacete|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=4 July 2023|accessdate=12 July 2023}}</ref> In 2014, he moved to [[Málaga CF]] and was initially assigned to the ''Cadete'' squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/2014/11/06/futbol/futbol_internacional/resto_de_america/1415292651.html|title=La saga de los Zalazar|trans-title=The saga of the Zalazar|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=6 November 2014|accessdate=12 July 2023}}</ref>

In 2018, after finishing his formation, Zalazar was promoted to Málaga's [[Atlético Malagueño|reserve team]] in [[Segunda División B]], but remained unregistered for the entire season after the club had no free registration spots;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eldesmarque.com/futbol/malaga-cf/20180901/asi-queda-la-plantilla-del-atletico-malagueno_120163406.html|title=Así queda la plantilla del Atlético Malagueño|trans-title=This is how the Atlético Malagueño squad end up|publisher=El Desmarque|language=es|date=1 September 2018|accessdate=12 July 2023}}</ref> he then refused a loan to a [[Tercera División]] side, as his contract was due to expire in the following summer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.merchanendirecto.es/futbol/incomprensible-melendez-y-rodri-zalazar-sin-ficha/|title=¡Incomprensible! Meléndez y Rodri Zalazar, sin ficha|trans-title=Incomprehensible! Meléndez and Rodri Zalazar, unregistered|publisher=Merchán en directo|language=es|date=3 September 2018|accessdate=12 July 2023}}</ref>

===Eintracht Frankfurt===
On 2 July 2019, Zalazar signed a four-year contract with [[Bundesliga]] club [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on 2 July 2019.<ref name="eintracht1">{{cite web|title=Eintracht Frankfurt sign Rodrigo Zalazar, could be sent out on loan|url=https://www.eintracht.de/en/news/article/eintracht-frankfurt-sign-rodrigo-zalazar-could-be-sent-out-on-loan-73838/|publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt|accessdate=27 July 2019}}</ref>

====Loan to Korona Kielce====
Three days after joining Eintracht Frankfurt, [[Ekstraklasa]] side [[Korona Kielce]] signed Zalazar on a one-year loan deal for [[2019–20 Ekstraklasa|2019–20]] season.<ref name="eintracht2">{{cite web|title=Rodrigo Zalazar loaned to Korona Kielce|url=https://www.eintracht.de/en/news/article/rodrigo-zalazar-loaned-to-korona-kielce-73910/|publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt|accessdate=27 July 2019}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 20 July 2019, coming on as a 70th minute substitute for [[Erik Pačinda]] in a 1–0 league win against [[Raków Częstochowa]].<ref name="pro debut">{{cite web|title=RAKÓW CZĘSTOCHOWA VS. KORONA KIELCE 1-0|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/07/20/poland/ekstraklasa/ks-rakow-czestochowa/mks-korona-kielce/3025704/|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=27 July 2019}}</ref>

Rarely used in the first team, Zalazar also played for [[Korona Kielce II]] in the [[III liga]], scoring three goals in 10 appearances.

====Loan to FC St. Pauli====
On 6 August 2020, [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[FC St. Pauli]] announced the signing of Zalazar on a season-long loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Der FC St. Pauli verpflichtet Mittelfeldspieler Rodrigo Zalazar|trans-title=FC St. Pauli signed midfielder Rodrigo Zalazar|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/news/der-fc-st-pauli-verpflichtet-rodrigo-zalazar/|publisher=FC St. Pauli|language=de|accessdate=6 August 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=St. Pauli leiht Rodrigo Zalazar von Eintracht Frankfurt aus |trans-title=St. Pauli is loaning Rodrigo Zalazar from Eintracht Frankfurt|url=https://www.kicker.de/st_pauli_leiht_zalazar_aus-781305/artikel |website=kicker |access-date=6 August 2020 |language=German |date=6 August 2020}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal on 19 October, netting the equalizer through a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]] in a 2–2 home draw against [[1. FC Nürnberg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/news/published/rodrigo-zalazar-speaks-to-the-press-after-the-nurnberg-game/|title=Zalazar: "I feel very much at home and try to show that on the pitch"|publisher=FC St. Pauli|date=21 October 2020|accessdate=12 July 2023}}</ref>

Zalazar finished the [[2020–21 2. Bundesliga|2020–21 season]] with six goals in 35 appearances overall, as St. Pauli finished in the 10th position.

===Schalke 04===
On 4 August 2021, Zalazar agreed to join fellow second division side [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] on a season-long loan with an option to make the move permanent until 2026.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/rodrigo-zalazar-joins-fc-schalke-04/|title=Rodrigo Zalazar joins FC Schalke 04|website=FC Schalke 04|date=4 August 2021}}</ref> On 25 March 2022, Schalke exercised this option, and he agreed to a permanent four-year contract with the club, effective as of 1 July.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/rodrigo-zalazar-signs-permanent-deal-with-fc-schalke-04/|title=Rodrigo Zalazar signs permanent deal with FC Schalke 04|website=Schalke 04|date=25 March 2022}}</ref> He finished [[2021–22 2. Bundesliga|the campaign]] as a regular starter as the club won promotion to the [[Bundesliga]] as champions, scoring the decisive goal in a 3–2 victory over St. Pauli that secured promotion.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://apnews.com/article/sports-business-soccer-hamburger-sv-europe-c1226895eb36e7b5ab31e9f48cf030f0 |title=Schalke promoted back to Bundesliga after one season away |publisher=AP News |date=7 May 2022 }}</ref>

Zalazar made his debut in the main category of German football on 7 August 2022, starting in a 3–1 away loss against [[1. FC Köln]]. He scored his first goal in the top tier six days later, netting the opener in a 2–2 home draw against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://schalke04.de/en/bundesliga-en/gladbach-report-home-2223/ |title=Last-minute Bülter penalty earns S04 a draw against Gladbach |publisher=FC Schalke 04 |date=13 August 2022 }}</ref>

In June 2023, after Schalke's [[2022–23 Bundesliga|relegation back to the second level]], newspaper ''[[Bild]]'' reported that Zalazar was seeking a move away from the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/schalke/wegen-marius-buelter-rodrigo-zalazar-fc-schalke-04-droht-transfer-stau-84291778.bild.html|title=Schalke droht Transfer-Stau|trans-title=Schalke threatens a transfer jam|publisher=[[Bild]]|language=de|date=11 June 2023|accessdate=12 July 2023}}</ref>

===Braga===
In July 2023, Zalazar joined [[Primeira Liga]] side [[S.C. Braga|Braga]], signing a four-year contract for a reported transfer fee of €6m.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/schalkes-rodrigo-zalazar-agrees-four-year-deal-at-braga-37843146 |title=Schalke’s Rodrigo Zalazar agrees four-year deal at Braga |publisher=OneFootball |date=13 July 2023 }}</ref>

===Sporting CP===
On 15 May 2026, [[Sporting CP]] announced the signing of Zalazar for a fee of €30 million, and a release clause of €80 million. This made him the most expensive transfer between two Portuguese clubs, surpassing the previous €20 million record Porto paid for [[David Carmo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Zalazar é a contratação mais cara de sempre entre clubes portugueses|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/zalazar-e-a-contratacao-mais-cara-de-sempre-entre-clubes-portugueses|language=pt|date=15 May 2026|access-date=16 May 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Spain to Uruguayan parents, Zalazar was eligible to represent both Uruguay and Spain at international level. While his older brother chose Spain, he followed his father's footsteps and chose to play for Uruguay.<ref name="radiouruguay">{{cite web|title=Rodrigo Zalazar nació en Albacete y eligió jugar para Uruguay|trans-title=Rodrigo Zalazar was born in Albacete and chose to play for Uruguay|publisher=Radio Uruguay|language=es|url=http://radiouruguay.uy/rodrigo-zalazar-nacio-en-albacete-y-eligio-jugar-para-uruguay/|accessdate=27 July 2019}}</ref>

Zalazar started to feature for the nation's [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|under-20]] team in 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malagacf.com/noticias/la-sub-20-uruguaya-cuenta-con-rodri|title=La Sub-20 uruguaya cuenta con Rodri|trans-title=The Uruguay under-20s count with Rodri|publisher=Málaga CF|language=es|date=12 June 2018|accessdate=12 July 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eldesmarque.com/futbol/malaga-cf/20180924/rodri-zalazar-campeon-con-uruguay-sub-20-en-catar_120165637.html|title=Rodri Zalazar, campeón con Uruguay sub 20 en Catar|trans-title=Rodri Zalazar, champion with Uruguay under-20s in Qatar|publisher=El Desmarque|language=es|date=24 September 2018|accessdate=12 July 2023}}</ref> being also included in [[Fabián Coito]]'s squad for the [[2019 South American U-20 Championship]] in January 2019.<ref name="auf"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Sub-20 Plantel para Chile 2019 |url=http://www.auf.org.uy/Portal/NEWS/15122/0/Sub20__Plantel_para_Chile_2019/|trans-title=Squad of the under-20s for Chile 2019 |publisher=AUF |date=19 December 2018 |language=Spanish |access-date=15 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116045859/http://www.auf.org.uy/Portal/NEWS/15122/0/Sub20__Plantel_para_Chile_2019/ |archive-date=16 January 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He played seven matches in the tournament, helping his team to finish third.

In June 2023, Zalazar received his first call-up to the [[Uruguay national football team|senior team]] for [[Exhibition game|friendly]] matches against [[Nicaragua national football team|Nicaragua]] and [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Siguen sumándose futbolistas convocados a los entrenamientos|trans-title=Footballers called up to trainings keep on joining|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/siguen-sumandose-futbolistas-convocados-a-los-entrenamientos/|publisher=AUF|language=es|date=5 June 2023|access-date=15 June 2023}}</ref> He made his debut on 14 June, scoring two goals in a 4–1 win against the former.<ref>{{cite web|title=Selección: Bielsa eligió a Matías Viña como capitán en un equipo con muchos debutantes|trans-title=National team: Bielsa chose Matías Viña as captain in a team with a lot of debutants|url=https://www.futbol.com.uy/Deportes/Seleccion-Bielsa-eligio-a-Matias-Vina-como-capitan-en-un-equipo-con-muchos-debutantes-uc856920|publisher=Fútbol.uy|language=es|date=14 June 2023|access-date=15 June 2023}}</ref> On 31 May 2026, he was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Rodrigo is the son of former Uruguay international footballer [[José Zalazar]], and the brother of former Spanish youth international [[Kuki Zalazar]]<ref name="eintracht3">{{cite web|title=Talented midfielder with an eye for goal|url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/talented-midfielder-with-an-eye-for-goal-73840|publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt|access-date=27 July 2019}}</ref> and [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] player [[Mauro Zalazar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/mauro-zalazar-transfer/|title=Mauro Zalazar moves to FC Schalke 04|website=FC Schalke 04|date=20 August 2024}}</ref> He was born in [[Albacete]], [[Castilla–La Mancha]], while his father was a player of the local club Albacete.<ref name="radiouruguay"/>

